    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-10-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-10-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="346"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d346">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72113 Au 7/36</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Alien Property Custodian</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sutherland</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-10-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 15, 1928</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Replying to your communication of October
                        13th,<note n="42" xml:id="d346fn42">Not printed.</note> with which you
                    enclosed a copy of the communication from His Excellency, the Austrian
                        Minister,<note n="43" xml:id="d346fn43">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_487">p. 487</ref>.</note>
                    which has reference to the transferring of funds belonging to the Austrian
                    Government, including the K. K. Oesterreichische Tabak Regie (Austrian Tobacco
                    Monopoly).</p>
                <p>You are advised that I have ordered the necessary procedure to be taken to comply
                    with this request.</p>
                <p>Very truly yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Howard Sutherland</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
